Fill in the missing memory units.

::: cloze
1024 bytes is one {=kilobyte|KB}, and 1024 of those is one {=megabyte|MB}.
:::

::: solution
The SI/binary distinction matters in practice, but in this course we treat one kilobyte as exactly 1024 bytes (the IEC binary prefix "kibibyte" / KiB is the precise term).
:::
